<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Credulous" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Credulous,</orth> apt to believe, easily deceived: <bibl n="shak. ven 986" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 986</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 1522" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1522</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.149" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 149</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.2.67" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 2, 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.2.195" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 2, 195</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.1.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 1, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.210" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 210</bibl>. Followed by <emph>in</emph>: <cit><quote>c. in this mad thought,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 2, 74</bibl></cit>. By <emph>of</emph>: <cit><quote>so c. of cure,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.1.118" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 1, 118</bibl></cit>. By <emph>to</emph>: <cit><quote>c. to false prints,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 2.4.130" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 4, 130</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>